  <b>Season 14</b> of <a href=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Jet_Lag:_Th=
e_Game" title=3D"Jet Lag: The Game">Jet Lag: The Game</a>, <i><b>Snake Acro=
ss South Korea</b></i> (sometimes called <b>SnaKe</b>), was teased by <a hr=
ef=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Sam_Denby" title=3D"Sam Denby">Sam Den=
by</a> on X <i>(Twitter)</i> where he made a post with the caption "We're S=
eoul back =F0=9F=87=B0=F0=9F=87=B7" while in <i>Seoul, South Korea</i>. Bec=
ause of this post, it would be a fair guess to assume that the next season =
of Jet Lag: The Game is taking place in South Korea, or has a board centere=
d around there.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Snake_Across_South_Korea#cite_note-1" aria-label=
=3D"Reference 1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>
<p></p><p>In an episode of The Layover, Sam Denby confirmed that this seaso=
n would be a new format. On the same episode Ben stated that this game requ=
ired a lot more thought than previous seasons.
</p><p>In the game design episode of <a href=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/w=
iki/The_Layover" title=3D"The Layover">the Layover</a><sup id=3D"cite_ref-:=
0_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Snake_=
Across_South_Korea#cite_note-:0-2" aria-label=3D"Reference 2"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>,=
 the game was revealed to be Snake.
</p><p>The game is a round-robin game similar to <a href=3D"https://jetlag.=
fandom.com/wiki/Tag_Across_Europe" title=3D"Tag Across Europe">Tag</a> and =
<a href=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Hide_%2B_Seek:_Japan" title=3D"Hi=
de + Seek: Japan">Hide + Seek</a>. One player takes role as the snaker, who=
 must travel the longest path possible on the South Korean train network. T=
he snaker may not take the same line or go to the same station that they've=
 been in before. Opposing them is the blockers, who can place obstacles ont=
o stations from their deck.=20
</p><p>The trailer for Snake Across South Korea released on June 4th, 2025 =
on Nebula and June 11th, 2025 on Youtube.
</p>
