<p>One player takes on the role of the <b>Snaker</b>, whose objective is to=
 create the <b>longest continuous path</b> possible by riding trains across=
 South Korea. The Snaker may travel freely but <b>cannot cross their own ro=
ute</b>, replicating the movement constraints of the traditional Snake game=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://jetlag.fando=
m.com/wiki/Snake_Across_South_Korea#cite_note-3" aria-label=3D"Reference 3"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> Opposing them are two <b>Blockers</b>, who travel independently=
 and attempt to <b>disrupt</b> the Snaker=E2=80=99s progress.=20
</p>
