<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Rules">Rules</span><span class=3D"mw-=
editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title=3D"Sig=
n in to edit" class=3D"mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label=3D"=
log-in-edit-section" data-action=3D"edit-section" href=3D"https://auth.fand=
om.com/signin?redirect=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fjetlag.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FSnake_Acr=
oss_South_Korea%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D2&amp;uselang=3Den&amp;metada=
ta=3Darticle-registration-edit-article-section" data-testid=3D"log-in-edit-=
section" aria-label=3D"Sign in to edit"><svg class=3D"wds-icon wds-icon-tin=
y" aria-hidden=3D"true" focusable=3D"false"><use xlink:href=3D"#wds-icons-p=
encil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></h4>
<ul><li>All travel must occur via the South Korean rail system (based on th=
e simplified map shown on screen).</li>
<li>The objective is to create the longest possible non-intersecting path o=
n the rail network as a Snaker. The overall time limit is 5 days (7AM-7PM e=
ach day).</li>
<li>Each player gets at least 1 run as a Snaker. Afterwards, each next Snak=
er is randomly chosen from the 2 players who do not currently have the winn=
ing run<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_2-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://j=
etlag.fandom.com/wiki/Snake_Across_South_Korea#cite_note-:0-2" aria-label=
=3D"Reference 2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup>.</li>
<li>Each run is limited to 18 hours.</li></ul>
<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Snaker">Snaker</span><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title=3D"S=
ign in to edit" class=3D"mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-label=
=3D"log-in-edit-section" data-action=3D"edit-section" href=3D"https://auth.=
fandom.com/signin?redirect=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fjetlag.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FSnake=
_Across_South_Korea%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D3&amp;uselang=3Den&amp;me=
tadata=3Darticle-registration-edit-article-section" data-testid=3D"log-in-e=
dit-section" aria-label=3D"Sign in to edit"><svg class=3D"wds-icon wds-icon=
-tiny" aria-hidden=3D"true" focusable=3D"false"><use xlink:href=3D"#wds-ico=
ns-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</s=
pan></span></h4>
<ul><li>The Snaker's goal is to make the longest possible non-intersecting =
path on the rail network.</li>
<li>When the Snaker passes through a <b>node</b> (a station with multiple i=
ntersecting lines), their progress for that run gets locked in, but they mu=
st also reveal their location to the Blockers.</li>
<li>If the Snaker goes to a station they have already passed through, or if=
 they fail a Roadblock or Battle Challenge, they <b>crash</b> and their run=
 is over.</li>
<li>The first snaker, <a href=3D"https://jetlag.fandom.com/wiki/Ben_Doyle" =
title=3D"Ben Doyle">Ben</a>, starts from Yongsan Station. Other runs start =
from wherever the last snaker crashed.</li></ul>
<h4><span class=3D"mw-headline" id=3D"Blockers">Blockers</span><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a title=
=3D"Sign in to edit" class=3D"mw-editsection-visualeditor" data-tracking-la=
bel=3D"log-in-edit-section" data-action=3D"edit-section" href=3D"https://au=
th.fandom.com/signin?redirect=3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fjetlag.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FSn=
ake_Across_South_Korea%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D4&amp;uselang=3Den&amp=
;metadata=3Darticle-registration-edit-article-section" data-testid=3D"log-i=
n-edit-section" aria-label=3D"Sign in to edit"><svg class=3D"wds-icon wds-i=
con-tiny" aria-hidden=3D"true" focusable=3D"false"><use xlink:href=3D"#wds-=
icons-pencil-tiny"></use></svg></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]=
</span></span></h4>
<ul><li>The Blockers work together to disrupt the Snaker's progress.</li>
<li>The Blockers get a 1-hour head start for each run. They can move freely=
 to interfere but must adhere to travel rules.</li>
<li>To impede the Snaker's progress, the Blockers may draw <b>cards</b>. Th=
ey can hold a maximum of five cards at a time.
<ul><li>They get 3 cards at the start of each round, and 1 card for each ad=
ditional node they visit.</li>
<li><b>Roadblocks</b> can be dropped on any station by successfully complet=
ing a challenge there. If the Snaker visits a roadblocked station, they mus=
t also complete the same challenge, or they crash.</li>
<li><b>Curses</b> can be dropped between 2 nodes. This card cannot crash a =
Snaker by itself, but it slows down their progress while in the affected se=
gment.</li>
<li><b>Battle Challenges</b> can be dropped on any station. These are compe=
titive mini-games played between the Blockers and Snaker at that station. W=
hen a Battle Challenge is declared, the Blockers find out what the mini-gam=
e is and may practice it, but the Snaker only finds out what it is upon arr=
iving at the station. If the Snaker loses, they crash. A Battle Challenge i=
s only active if the Blockers are already waiting at that station when the =
Snaker arrives.</li>
<li><b>Powerups</b> are miscellaneous cards that help the Blockers in some =
way (e.g., Discard 1 / Draw 2, secret block).</li>
<li>If the Blockers drop a Roadblock, Curse, or Battle Challenge, they must=
 inform the Snaker and thus reveal their current location.</li></ul></li></=
ul>
